  "prompt": "How do you reduce NOX emissions in car?",
  "response": "To reduce NOx (nitrogen oxides) emissions in cars, several methods can be employed:\n\n1. Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)\n- Recirculates a portion of exhaust gases back into the engine\n- Lowers combustion temperature, reducing NOx formation\n\n2. Selective Catalytic Reduction (SCR)\n- Injects urea/diesel exhaust fluid into exhaust stream\n- Converts NOx into nitrogen and water through a catalytic converter\n\n3. Advanced Engine Design\n- Optimized combustion chamber design\n- Improved fuel injection systems\n- Lower combustion temperatures\n\n4. Catalytic Converters\n- Uses precious metals to convert NOx into less harmful gases\n- Reduces emissions before they exit the exhaust system\n\n5. Low-NOx Fuel\n- Using cleaner, low-sulfur fuels\n- Reduces potential for NOx formation during combustion\n\n6. Hybrid and Electric Vehicles\n- Produce fewer or no direct NOx emissions\n- Reduce overall vehicle emissions\n\n7. Regular Vehicle Maintenance\n- Keeping engine tuned\n- Replacing air and fuel filters\n- Ensuring proper combustion efficiency\n\nThese techniques help automotive manufacturers and owners reduce harmful NOx emissions, improving air quality and environmental sustainability.",
